Package: cirBEM
Title: Beta Regression Cosinor Models for Circadian Methylation Analysis
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: person("yx", "h",
    email = "yixiang.hong@uth.tmc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits cosinor-based beta regression models for detecting circadian
    rhythmicity in DNA methylation array data. Supports fixed-effects
    (cross-sectional) and mixed-effects (repeated measures) designs with
    configurable period. Implements empirical Bayes shrinkage of the beta
    distribution precision parameter across CpG sites, analogous to limma's
    moderated variance, to improve genome-wide inference. Provides amplitude,
    phase, and MESOR estimation on both logit-link and response scales.
